PSCU @PeopleDailyKe First Lady Margaret Kenyatta has vowed to carry on with efforts to take healthcare services closer to Kenyans in all parts of the country. Speaking at Makutano Stadium, West Pokot County, where she officially launched the 3rd Beyond Zero Medical Safari yesterday, the First Lady emphasised her commitment to ensure Kenyans, especially mothers and children, are protected from preventable illnesses and deaths. “I believe that everyone – girls and boys, men and women – must have a chance to reach their full potential; an opportunity to pursue their dreams,” she said. second phase of the First Lady’s efforts to boost healthcare services in the country through her Beyond Zero Initiative. The first phase entailed the delivery of fully equipped mobile clinics to all the 47 counties